        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 4 at 8:53PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 852 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Tabor City, or 14 miles southwest of Whiteville, moving northeast at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Whiteville, Tabor City, Chadbourn, Bladenboro, Hallsboro, Redbug,
Mollie, Sidney, Southeastern Community College, Clarendon, Williams,
Brunswick, Clarkton, and Columbus Regional Healthcare System.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
